$ /tmp

Usually a world writable directory used as a scratch space.

It's often cleared when a system is rebooted. To keep temporary data accross reboots, use → Linux/fhs/var/tmp[`/var/tmp`].

Usually, the `/tmp` directory has the → Linux/filesystem/file-directory-metadata#sticky-bit[sticky bit] set.

sa:
  → Linux/fhs/dev/shm
